<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 12 at 5:11PM EST  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of
northwestern Pittsylvania, southern Bedford, northern Henry and
Franklin Counties through 615 PM EST...
At 510 PM EST, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Goodview to near Rocky Mount to Philpott
Dam. Movement was east at 40 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Bedford...
Rocky Mount...
Stewartsville...
Huddleston...
Moneta...
Penhook...
and Callands.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
